This paper deals with the application of massive MIMO in a cellular network, which involves the use of multiple antennas at each access point to serve multiple users simultaneously. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses power allocation and optimization, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of multiple antennas and distributed beamforming is a key aspect of the paper, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and architecture (cs.AR).
